\pard\hyphpar0\widctlpar\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ulnone\b Specification:\b0\f1\fs24\lang4105\par
\f0\lang9\tab The main goal of this program is to create a RPG game in a "cowboy western" theme, using characters from the graphic novel "Don't Fear the OOP". We have decided on our main battle mechanic being an intense match of "wild wild west", where players every few seconds either choose to shoot, reload, or dodge. If one player shoots while the other player reloads, and the one player has ammo from reloading, that player wins. The game will be a top-down real-time game like pokemon, where the player can choose to move in any which direction, into and around buildings how they like. In these buildings, players can get drunk and can play different minigames such as chess, black jack, and tic tac toe. AI will need to be decently performing but not too good in all of these games so that it poses a challenge while not being impossible to beat. Furthermore, the AI must improve as the game goes on, especially in the wild-wild-west game. Currency in the game will be represented as Damsels, and in each game Damsels can be used as gambling money, eg gambing 2 Damsels where if you win you get 4 and if you lose you lose your 2 Damsels. During games of wild-wild-west, if you die all your damsels will be lost that you are currently bringing with you. Damsels can be used to buy more ammo capacity for your gun in wild-wild-west games, and to buy more hats which represent lives in the game, if you lose all your hats you lose the game. If the character dies they wake up in the hotel\f1\lang4105\par
